{
  "texts": [
    "In addition, synthetic clinical text generated by large LMs may enable better identification of rare events documented in the EHR, although more work is needed to optimize generation methods.",
    "Our fine-tuned models were less prone to bias than ChatGPT-family models and outperformed for most SDoH classes, especially any SDoH mentions, despite being orders of magnitude smaller.",
    "In the future, these models could improve our understanding of drivers of health disparities by improving real-world evidence and could directly support patient care by flagging patients who may benefit most from proactive resource and social work referral.",
    "Table 4 describes the patient populations of the datasets used in this study.",
    "Gender and race/ethnicity data and descriptors were collected from the EHR."
  ]
}